pop, observes what goes on in the hamam, and wonders about Arabesk culture.The book features discussions of queer travel writers, poets, playwrights, and film directors. Their multifarious works manifest the subtle and subversive ways in which artists crisscross the cultural borders of East and West. With its many facets of Turkish-Euro-American cultural interactions, Queer Turkey outlines a kaleidoscope of transnational poetics.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2021: Frontlist Collection  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aCultural Studies. 4aCulture. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aIstanbul. 4aLGBTQ. 4aOrientalism. 4aPopular Culture. 4aQueer Theory. 4aSexuality. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aIstanbul.  aLGBTQ.  aOrientalism.  aPopular Culture.  aQueer Theory.  aSexuality.2 aKnowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2021: Frontlist Collectionefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Ottoman Turkish Studies eBooks 2021z978311075670808iTitle is part of eBo